(438, 1, '2017-02-01 20:01:41', '2017-02-01 20:01:41', 'Literacy Chicago is a nonprofit organization that empowers individuals to achieve greater self sufficiency through language and literacy instruction.\n<div class="column-1-2">\n<h4>History</h4>\nIn 1968, two organizations—Literacy Volunteers of Chicago and Literacy Council of Chicago—separately formed to address the needs of Chicago adults in the areas of language and literacy. Both successful in their missions to connect tutors and students, the groups merged in 1992 to establish a larger and stronger single organization called Literacy Chicago. For more than four decades, literally thousands of area adults have participated in the broad range of programs Literacy Chicago has developed, including basic literacy, GED preparation, English as a Second Language. Workforce Development, Citizenship Program, and Transportation bridge program. Literacy Chicago continues its learner-focused programming by relying heavily on the efforts of volunteer tutors, and frequently offers ancillary classes such as health literacy, computer literacy, and financial literacy, to support the language/literacy options.\n\n</div>\n<!--nextpage-->\n<div class="entry-header">\n<h1 class="entry-title">CAREERS</h1>\n</div>\n<div class="entry-container">\n<div class="entry-content"><article><strong>Position Title: ABE/ GED Instructor – Literacy Chicago</strong>\n\n<strong>Summary: </strong>This part time position will be responsible in instructing an offsite GED class. Four days a week total of 12 hours. The ABE/GED teacher will instruct students (18 and older) who want to obtain a credential equivalent to a high school diploma. They must be trained in adult education instructional techniques.\n\n<strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</strong>  ABE/GED teachers instruct students in the areas of math, science, writing, reading and social studies, the five areas covered in the GED tests. They may be required to assess students in order to create a learning program for each student. They also evaluate and test students, either formally or informally to determine if students are progressing. A GED teacher may help students with improving their critical thinking, problem-solving, information processing and communication skills. Students in these classes will be performing between levels 6-8.9 and 9-12.9 in reading level.\n\n<strong>In addition:</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Asses individuals education plans with each student that includes strengths and weaknesses based on TABE, learning styles and student needs</li>\n 	<li>Integrate authentic material within GED subject areas.</li>\n 	<li>Employ teaching methodology that reflects best practices, addresses diverse needs and leaning styles as well as user integrated curriculums.</li>\n 	<li>Create lesson plans and provide plans as requested</li>\n 	<li>Integrate computer lab and GED software with classroom insturcti0on as appropriate</li>\n 	<li>Attend weekly /monthly instructor meetings</li>\n 	<li>Attend workshops for professional development related to classroom and students needs.</li>\n 	<li>Share information with fellow colleagues</li>\n 	<li>Submit monthly reports as required</li>\n 	<li>Track attendance and class achievement for reporting purposes</li>\n 	<li>Perform other duties as necessary</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>ABE/ GED Teacher Job Requirements: </strong>Minimum BA Degree. However, Masters preferred in Adult Education, Teaching, or related field. Experience in teaching adult learners, able to work with diverse populations. The GED instructor needs to be highly motivated, energetic, dynamic and Student focused. Excellent oral and communication skills are a must.\n\n<strong>Salary Range: To be determined /Commensurate with Experience</strong>\n\n<strong>Date Posted: November 21, 2016</strong>\n\n<strong>Application Deadlines: December 7, 2016</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Interested parties may send resume and cover letter to: </strong><a href="mailto:info@literacychicago.org"><strong>info@literacychicago.org</strong></a><strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>Please include GED Instructor in the subject line</strong>\n\n</article></div>\n</div>\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h4>Sponsors</h4>\nWhole Foods\n\n[content_chunk id="320"]', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-02-01 20:01:41', '2017-02-01 20:01:41', '', 18, 'http://localhost:8888/2017/02/01/18-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
